          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "As a young girl, you were always by your fathers side, in the woods. Your mother died at a young age, and your father trained you like he would a son. You learned tracking and hunting, and when what you could not take from the land was enough, you worked at a Lumber Mill in the fall and winter. Eventually your reputation grew and the Police, called you in for help tracking criminals who has fled into the forest. Eventually, you became so good that the FBI brought you on as a special contractor.  One night, you noticed an odd set of tracks in your forest, and started tracking whatever it was. An hour before dawn, you found your quarry - and, unbeknownst to you, had passed a crucial test. Your sire only wanted to bring the best into the clan, and someone who could find him in the forest at night was definitely among the best. Together, you criss-crossed the country for nearly 20 years, becoming among the best trackers even among the Gangrel. Then, one night, you stumbled into some sacred shrine for Lupines - the werewolves who kill vampires on sight. You lived, your sire didn't. You fled the woods and joined up with an Anarch gang in Central California. While some parts of Anarch philosophy appeal to you, you realize they'll never achieve what they want until they can stop getting in each other's way. You have spent little time in the Camarilla, and while you know the rules, politics are still a mystery to you. But you appreciate a more structured society, and feel ready to contribute what you can to vampire society. You still maintain a few Anarch ties, but know it would go poorly for you if anyone ever found out.",
